<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="116" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,777,618,644]" box="[151,777,618,644]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicName authority="plorans (Charpentier, 1825)" authorityName="plorans (Charpentier" authorityYear="1825" box="[151,777,618,644]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Eyprepocnemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="plorans" subSpecies="plorans">
<emphasis box="[151,525,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">Eyprepocnemis plorans plorans</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[532,777,618,644]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">(Charpentier, 1825)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,690,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">Very common throughout much of the year, generally within a broad range of wetland habitats, as also in mesic environments.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="116" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,690,789]" box="[199,1267,762,789]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,762,788]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">Distribution</emphasis>
. Mediterranean as well as in parts of the Afrotropical and Middle Eastern regions.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,663,870,896]" box="[151,663,870,896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">
<taxonomicName authority="(Redtenbacher, 1889)" baseAuthorityName="Redtenbacher" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[151,663,870,896]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Heteracris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersa">
<emphasis box="[151,390,870,896]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">Heteracris adspersa</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[397,663,870,896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">(Redtenbacher, 1889)</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,942,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">
A highly localized species, known from a single coastal locality, Salina, where numbers tend to fluctuate noticeably from year to year. Although it occurs within a Natura 2000 site, the area on which the population thrives is quite small and is subject to seasonal flooding by freshwater run-off. Such circumstances make the population all the more vulnerable. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Redtenbacher" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[389,525,1050,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Heteracris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersa">
<emphasis box="[389,525,1050,1076]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">H. adspersa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
features on the IUCN Red List and is considered ‘Vulnerable’ with a ‘decreasing population trend’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Hochkirch, A. &amp; Massa, B. &amp; Presa, J. J. &amp; Siedle, K. &amp; Korsunovskaya, O." box="[357,608,1086,1113]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116" pagination="16084630" refId="ref7839" refString="Hochkirch, A., Massa, B., Presa, J. J., Siedle, K. &amp; Korsunovskaya, O. (2016) Heteracris adspersa. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, 2016, e. T 16084630 A 74493895. Available from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org / species / 16084630 / 74493895 (accessed 18 September 2020)" type="journal article" year="2016">
Hochkirch 
<emphasis box="[484,541,1086,1112]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,942,1221]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1122,1148]" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[361,527,1122,1148]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">
H. a. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Redtenbacher" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[426,527,1122,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Heteracris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersa">adspersa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is common in parts of the Afrotropical, Middle Eastern and Eastern Palaearctic regions. 
<taxonomicName authority="Galvagni, 1978" authorityName="Galvagni" authorityYear="1978" box="[248,652,1158,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Baissogryllidae" genus="Heteracris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="116" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="adspersa" subSpecies="massai">
<emphasis box="[248,470,1158,1184]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">H. adspersa massai</emphasis>
Galvagni, 1978
</taxonomicName>
occurs in Sardinia and Sicily; it is likely that the taxon that occurs in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,216,1194,1220]" name="Malta" pageId="9" pageNumber="116">Malta</collectingCountry>
and North Africa belongs to this subspecies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
